      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Method of manufactured solutions (MMS) applied to all governing equations including hemolysis transport scalar.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was completed for Navier-Stokes and continuity equations. The hemolysis power-law scalar transport equation was verified against analytical benchmarks only at low shear rates; high-shear regime verification is absent, limiting the achieved level to 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Richardson extrapolation on at least three systematically refined meshes; GCI reported for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three mesh levels were run (coarse 3M, medium 8M, fine 20M cells). Richardson extrapolation and GCI were computed for pressure rise; GCI for the hemolysis index was estimated but the medium-to-fine refinement ratio did not meet the 1.3 minimum recommended, reducing confidence. Achieved level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental boundary conditions (inlet velocity profile, fluid temperature, hematocrit) must be replicated in the simulation to within ±5% of measured values.",
      "rationale": "Inlet velocity profiles and fluid temperature were matched to within ±4%. However, hematocrit was fixed at a nominal 33% in the simulation while experimental measurements ranged 31–36%, introducing a condition mismatch that limits the factor to level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E% or validation uncertainty U_val) computed for hemolysis index at all five operating points with uncertainty bands overlapping.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative E% and U_val were computed for three of five operating points. Experiments were performed across all five points, but summary statistics for operating points 2 and 4 were extracted from a compiled report without individual-run uncertainty decomposition, preventing full quantitative comparison at those conditions."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must map directly to the clinical acceptance threshold used in the regulatory submission.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the direct QoI and maps to the clinical threshold. Platelet activation index (PAI) was identified as a secondary QoI relevant to chronic VAD use but was not computed in this assessment, preventing level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation experiments must use the same pump geometry, blood analogue fluid, and operating envelope as the COU. Continuous-flow VAD duty cycle must be represented.",
      "rationale": "The FDA generic pump geometry and a glycerol-water blood analogue were used. Five operating points span the COU envelope. Long-duration (>6 h) continuous operation was not tested in the validation experiments, which used 30-minute steady-state runs, limiting relevance to the chronic VAD duty cycle."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Residuals for continuity, momentum, and scalar transport must converge to below 1e-5; iterative convergence of NIH must be demonstrated.",
      "rationale": "Continuity and momentum residuals reached 1e-5. The hemolysis scalar residual stalled at 3e-4 for operating point 4 due to impeller-volute interaction unsteadiness; a phase-averaged workaround was applied but not fully documented, limiting the achieved level to 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent review of simulation setup files and post-processing scripts by a reviewer not involved in model construction.",
      "rationale": "An internal peer review of the simulation setup was conducted, but the reviewer had participated in boundary condition specification for two of the five operating points, reducing independence. No external review was performed. Achieved level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection justified by sensitivity study; hemolysis power-law constants sourced from peer-reviewed literature with uncertainty bounds propagated.",
      "rationale": "The k-omega SST turbulence model was selected without a formal sensitivity study comparing alternative models (e.g., RSM or LES). Hemolysis power-law constants (C, alpha, beta) were taken from Giersiepen et al. without uncertainty propagation. These gaps substantially limit the model form credibility to level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
