    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Despite multiple credibility factor gaps, the assessment team accepted the package for regulatory submission on the basis that the hemolysis index predictions fall below the clinical threshold with margin across all five operating points, and Monte Carlo UQ confirms the margin is robust to input uncertainty. Outstanding gaps in model form, equivalency of input parameters, and test sample characterization are acknowledged as epistemic limitations to be addressed in a follow-on MRL 5 re-assessment. Provenance records for validation result generation were partially reconstructed from laboratory notebooks; two results (operating points 2 and 4) were ingested from compiled summary reports and their generation activities were not individually traceable in the structured record.",
